  <text>
      <body>
        
     
      <div xml:id="Sonnet41"> 
              <interpGrp type="poembox">
                <interp ana="#form" type="free"></interp>
                <interp ana="#tone" type="sad"></interp>
                <interp ana="#topic" type="society"></interp>
              </interpGrp>
             <lg> 
              <l>Little boy, nothing has been said about your fear;</l>
          <l>the sky projects your growth and in this sudden blackout</l> 
          <l>ghost foreknow the naked stars that will skin you alive.</l>
          <l>Your voice distant, buried deep in your toys, the year uncatalogued,</l>
          <l>and yet the cruel clock of war's evening answers,</l>
          <l>each hour falters, autographs your lean gaze.</l>
          <l>I tell you past the impersonal sanctum of high scholars:</l>
          <l>fear breeds hate and death brings no taste of godliness,</l>
          <l>yet count the saints, while ogres strike your day</l>
          <l>I am tired of your retouched photo under glass,</l>
          <l>of your cinema orbits where flamingos sleep,</l>
          <l>of your uncomplaining grave, politely adult.</l>
         
                 
